metaData <- read.delim("C:/WORK/CUET_2022_CONF/satellite_images_LST/2001/LE07_L1TP_137044_20010419_20170205_01_T1/LE07_L1TP_137044_20010419_20170205_01_T1_MTL.txt",

Lsat <- stackMeta("C:/WORK/CUET_2022_CONF/satellite_images_LST/2001/LE07_L1TP_137044_20010419_20170205_01_T1/LE07_L1TP_137044_20010419_20170205_01_T1_MTL.txt")

plotRGB(Lsat, r = 3, g = 2, b = 1, stretch = "hist")

Here, C:/WORK/CUET_2022_CONF/satellite_images_LST/2001/LE07_L1TP_137044_20010419_20170205_01_T1/ is the directory where the satellite image bands are located. LE07_L1TP_137044_20010419_20170205_01_T1_MTL.txt is the metadata file.

Load the shapefile of the area of interest, crop & mask and plot .

shape <- shapefile("DCC_UTM_46N.shp")
Lsat_shape <- crop(Lsat, extent(shape))
Lsat_shape <- mask(Lsat_shape, shape)
plotRGB(Lsat_shape, r = 3, g = 2, b = 1, stretch = "hist")

Required formula for LST calculation

  1. Spectral_Radiance_L = ((Lmax-Lmin)/(QCalmax-QCalmin)) * (Lsat_shape$B6_dn - QCalmin) + Lmin
  2. At_satellite_temp = K2/ (ln((K1/Spectral_Radiance_L)+1))
  3. Surface_temp = (At_satellite_temp/(1+(waveLenAt_satellite_temp/rho) ln(emissivity))) - 273.15

emissivity = 0.004* Pv + 0.986

Pv = (NDVI - minValue(NDVI))/(maxValue(NDVI) - minValue(NDVI))**2

Reading required values from the metadata. The code is slightly changed for Landsat -5. (omit VCID_1)

Wave length of the emitted radiance for Band six (thermal band) is taken as the average of of 10.4 & 12.5. Rho = 14388 (constant)

waveLen <- 11.4
rho<- 14388

Lmax <- as.numeric(metaData[grep('RADIANCE_MAXIMUM_BAND_6_VCID_1', metaData$GROUP),]$L1_METADATA_FILE)
Lmin <- as.numeric(metaData[grep('RADIANCE_MINIMUM_BAND_6_VCID_1', metaData$GROUP),]$L1_METADATA_FILE)

QCalmax <- as.numeric(metaData[grep('QUANTIZE_CAL_MAX_BAND_6_VCID_1', metaData$GROUP),]$L1_METADATA_FILE)
QCalmin <- as.numeric(metaData[grep('QUANTIZE_CAL_MIN_BAND_6_VCID_1', metaData$GROUP),]$L1_METADATA_FILE)

K2 <- as.numeric(metaData[grep('K2_CONSTANT_BAND_6_VCID_1', metaData$GROUP),]$L1_METADATA_FILE)
K1 <- as.numeric(metaData[grep('K1_CONSTANT_BAND_6_VCID_1', metaData$GROUP),]$L1_METADATA_FILE)

Calculating Spectral Radiance and At-Satellite Temperature. The code is slightly changed for Landsat -5. (omit VCID_1)

Spectral_Radiance_L <- ((Lmax-Lmin)/(QCalmax-QCalmin)) * (Lsat_shape$B6_VCID_1_dn - QCalmin) + Lmin
At_satellite_temp <- K2/ (ln((K1/Spectral_Radiance_L)+1))

Calculating the At-Surface Temperature

NDVI Calculation

Lsat_shape_ndvi <- spectralIndices(Lsat_shape, red = "B3_dn", nir = "B4_dn", indices = "NDVI")
plot(Lsat_shape_ndvi, main = "NDVI")

Proportion of Vegetation and Emissivity

Pv<-(Lsat_shape_ndvi - minValue(Lsat_shape_ndvi))/(maxValue(Lsat_shape_ndvi) - minValue(Lsat_shape_ndvi))**2

emissivity <- 0.004* Pv + 0.986

Calculating At-Surface Temperature and Plot

Surface_temp<-(At_satellite_temp/(1+(waveLen*At_satellite_temp/rho)* ln(emissivity))) - 273.15
plot(Surface_temp, col=brewer.pal(9,"YlOrRd"), main = "Land Surface Temperature (LST)")

Reclassify the LST Raster

reclass_df <- c(-Inf, 26, 1,
                26, 29, 2,
                29, 32, 3,
                32, Inf, 4)


reclass_matrix <- matrix(reclass_df,
                    ncol = 3,
                    byrow = TRUE)

reclass_matrix
##      [,1] [,2] [,3]
## [1,] -Inf   26    1
## [2,]   26   29    2
## [3,]   29   32    3
## [4,]   32  Inf    4
LST_classified <- reclassify(Surface_temp,
                             reclass_matrix)

View number of Pixels in each category

barplot(LST_classified,
        main = "Number of pixels in each class")

freq(LST_classified)
##      value  count
## [1,]     1  60161
## [2,]     2 190033
## [3,]     3  80453
## [4,]     4   3748
## [5,]    NA 199425

Plot Re-classified data

plot(LST_classified,
     legend = FALSE,
     col = brewer.pal(4,"YlOrRd"), axes = FALSE,
     main = "LST Zones (Degree Celcius)")

legend("left",
       legend = c("Low Temperature (<26)", "Mid-Temperature (26-29)", 
                  "Higher Temperature (29-32)", "Very High Temperature (>32)"),
       fill = brewer.pal(4,"YlOrRd"), cex= 0.5,
       border = FALSE,
       bty = "n")
